>You wouldn't even have to electrically insulate it...ground the negative
>terminal of the 6v battery to the frame/body, then run a single 6v+ wire
>to the heater. Disconnect the wire that would normally supply voltage
>to the heater and connect the 6V+ wire to it. The ground is the
>return path to the battery.  You are correct, though...you would have
>recharge the 6V battery often...



